Sticky wings make a fantastic appetizer for friends and family. Together with fries or pasta, sticky wings can go really well depending on your preference. Ingredients Preparation Step 1 Rinse the chicken wings with salty water. Step 2 Separate each wing at the joint into two pieces. Step 3 In a bowl, place the wings and the drums and pour in soy sauce, ginger, garlic powder and lemon juice. Toss well to coat and refrigerate for 2 hours. Step 4 Remove from fridge and season with salt and pepper. Step 5 In a pan, over medium heat, put the oil and coat the wings with honey as you saut√©. Step 6 Fry each side until brown for 5 minutes. Step 7 Coat with sesame seeds as desired and serve while warm. Step 8 Enjoy with a cold glass of mango juice over fries.